## 6. Parametric Insurance Model

Parametric insurance is based on predefined triggers rather than manual verification.

### Example Triggers

| Disruption Type | Trigger Condition      | Payout |
| --------------- | ---------------------- | ------ |
| Heavy Rain      | Rainfall > 50mm/day    | ₹300   |
| Heatwave        | Temperature > 45°C     | ₹250   |
| Pollution       | AQI > 400              | ₹200   |
| Curfew          | Government restriction | ₹400   |

---

## 7. Weekly Pricing Model

### Rationale

* Aligns with gig worker income cycles
* Affordable and flexible
* Reduces financial burden

### Pricing Formula

Weekly Premium = Base Rate + Risk Factor + Location Multiplier

**Example:**

* Base Rate: ₹20
* High-risk zone: +₹10
* Pollution factor: +₹5

Final Premium: ₹35/week

